HEADWORD: Pangolin
<hw>Pan"go*lin</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧"g⟦osl⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Malay <ets>pang⟦umac⟧lang</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of <gen>Manis</gen>,
<gen>Pholidotus</gen>, and related genera, found in Africa and Asia.
They are covered with imbricated scales, and feed upon ants. Called also
<altname>scaly ant-eater</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pangothic</ent>⟦br⟧
